Dear friends and residents,
I wish I could tell you that we woke up to a new day. But no.
Over 26 hours since the incident began, there is still fighting in the kibbutz. The army has not yet managed to take control of the terrorists. Evacuations continue but so is the fighting, and the evacuation plan/map is not clear and not prioritized by us but by the army. Since there has been no communication since yesterday with our security personnel in the kibbutz - the army essentially doesn't communicate directly with us, the kibbutz management, because "we are civilians".
CENSORED and I are now working with all our might to establish direct contact with the army so they understand that the key to minimizing, even slightly, the terrible damage, is in the management and directing of the searches and evacuation by the kibbutz management. People are in mortal danger.
If necessary, we will also go to the media because the army is not...
Many of you have contacted me and others in the emergency team privately. That's fine, that's excellent. I wish we had more good news to share. We know about every family of wounded, of those without contact, of people who are under attack right now - we know. I believe in transparency and as I tell many of you privately, any piece of information we have - we will pass on to you.
You are dear to me and to the entire management. We are at your disposal whether there is information or not.
I very much hope that in the coming hours we will know much more and begin the terrible task of rehabilitation that comes "after". We are not there yet.
Embracing you all
CENSORED
